dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.systemtemplate.securecommunication

Interface IIPSecRule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity, IIdentifiable, IReferrable

    public interface IIPSecRule
extends IEntity, IIdentifiable
    IIPSecRule: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    This element defines an IPsec rule that describes communication traffic that is monitored, protected and filtered.

      • getRemotePortRangeStart

        long getRemotePortRangeStart()
        Query the value of the attribute RemotePortRangeStart.

        This attribute restricts the traffic monitoring to tcp and defines a start value for the remote port range. If this attribute is not set then this rule shall be effective for all local ports. Please note that port ranges are currently not supported in the AUTOSAR AP’s operating system backend. If AP systems are involved, each IPsec rule may only contain a single port.

        Returns:
        The value or null
